data.title: Forester
data.description: forester is a collection of open source libraries of Java and Ruby software for phylogenomics and evolutionary biology research
data.name: forester

evidence: Commands are invoked as standalone Java applications, e.g. `java -cp path/to/forester.jar org.forester.application.hmmscan_seq_extract` and `java -Xmx8048m path/to/forester.jar org.forester.application.cladinator3`, indicating end-user programs rather than libraries.
Tools operate on domain scientific data such as `hmmscan output`, `fasta file`, and phylogenetic `input tree(s) file`, implying direct use in bioinformatics/phylogenetic analysis workflows.

Distribution is described via a JAR on the classpath (`path/to/forester.jar`) with no mention of package managers, containers, or binaries, implying users obtain and run it from the source repository or its built JAR.
